@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title MLOps LEGO Minifigure Classification - Control Flow

actor User
participant "get_data.py" as GetData
participant "Kaggle API" as Kaggle
participant "train_model.py" as Train
participant "MLflow Tracking" as MLflowTrack
participant "AWS S3" as S3
participant "MLflow Registry" as Registry
participant "Prefect Orchestrator" as Prefect
participant "Batch Service\n(Docker)" as Batch
participant "Stream Service\n(Docker)" as Stream
participant "streaming_send_data.py" as StreamData
participant "Evidently Service" as Evidently
participant "MongoDB" as Mongo
participant "Prometheus" as Prom
participant "Grafana" as Graf

== Data Acquisition ==
User -> GetData: Execute get_data.py
activate GetData
GetData -> Kaggle: Download LEGO dataset
activate Kaggle
Kaggle --> GetData: Dataset files
deactivate Kaggle
GetData --> User: Data ready
deactivate GetData

== Model Training ==
User -> Train: Execute train_model.py
activate Train
Train -> Train: Load and preprocess data
Train -> MLflowTrack: Start experiment
activate MLflowTrack
Train -> Train: Train fastai model
Train -> MLflowTrack: Log parameters & metrics
Train -> S3: Store model artifacts
activate S3
S3 --> Train: Artifacts stored
deactivate S3
Train -> MLflowTrack: Register model version
MLflowTrack -> Registry: Create model version
activate Registry
Registry --> MLflowTrack: Version registered
MLflowTrack --> Train: Experiment logged
deactivate MLflowTrack
Train --> User: Training complete
deactivate Train

== Model Promotion ==
User -> Registry: Promote model to production
activate Registry
Registry -> Registry: Update model stage
Registry --> User: Model promoted
deactivate Registry

== Batch Prediction Workflow ==
User -> Prefect: Deploy batch_prefect_flow
activate Prefect
Prefect -> Prefect: Schedule batch job
Prefect -> Batch: Trigger batch prediction
activate Batch
Batch -> Registry: Load production model
activate Registry
Registry --> Batch: Model artifacts
deactivate Registry
Batch -> Batch: Run predictions on batch data
Batch -> Evidently: Send prediction data
activate Evidently
Evidently -> Mongo: Store metrics
activate Mongo
Mongo --> Evidently: Stored
deactivate Mongo
Evidently -> Prom: Export metrics
activate Prom
Prom --> Evidently: Metrics exported
deactivate Prom
Evidently --> Batch: Monitoring complete
deactivate Evidently
Batch --> Prefect: Batch complete
deactivate Batch
Prefect --> User: Workflow complete
deactivate Prefect

== Stream Prediction Workflow ==
User -> StreamData: Execute streaming_send_data.py
activate StreamData
StreamData -> Stream: Send image data (stream)
activate Stream
Stream -> Registry: Load production model
activate Registry
Registry --> Stream: Model artifacts
deactivate Registry
Stream -> Stream: Predict classification
Stream -> Evidently: Send prediction event
activate Evidently
Evidently -> Mongo: Store real-time metrics
activate Mongo
Mongo --> Evidently: Stored
deactivate Mongo
Evidently -> Prom: Export metrics
activate Prom
Prom --> Evidently: Metrics exported
deactivate Prom
Evidently --> Stream: Monitoring complete
deactivate Evidently
Stream --> StreamData: Prediction result
deactivate Stream
StreamData --> User: Streaming complete
deactivate StreamData

== Monitoring & Visualization ==
User -> Graf: Access dashboard
activate Graf
Graf -> Prom: Query metrics
activate Prom
Prom -> Evidently: Fetch monitoring data
activate Evidently
Evidently -> Mongo: Retrieve metrics
activate Mongo
Mongo --> Evidently: Metrics data
deactivate Mongo
Evidently --> Prom: Monitoring metrics
deactivate Evidently
Prom --> Graf: Metrics data
deactivate Prom
Graf --> User: Display dashboards
deactivate Graf

== CI/CD Pipeline ==
User -> User: Push code changes
User -> "GitHub Actions" as CI: Trigger CI workflow
activate CI
CI -> CI: Run unit tests
CI -> CI: Run integration tests
CI -> CI: Run linting (pylint)
CI -> CI: Run formatting check (black)
CI --> User: CI results
deactivate CI

@enduml
